'''Avraham Hermoni''' (May 10, 1926- June 24, 2006) was an [[Israelis|Israeli]] [[chemist]], government official, scientific counselor in the [[Israeli embassy in Washington, DC|Israeli embassy in Washington]], and a senior technical director at [[RAFAEL]], Israel’s national center for weapons development.

==Biography==
Hermoni’s involvement in the [[Israeli nuclear program]] was instrumental to its ultimate success. Between 1959 and 1969 he served as technical director (equivalent to vice president) at RAFAEL. His main duties included overseeing and planning RAFAEL’s work on Israel’s nuclear weapons.<ref>http://www.wilsoncenter.org/avraham-hermoni#hermonibio</ref>

==Bibliography==
