{{Infobox lake | name = Lewiston Lake | image = Lewiston dam us bor.jpg | caption = Lewiston Dam on the Trinity River forming the lake behind | location = [[Trinity County, California]] | coords = {{coord|40|43|35|N|122|46|59|W|region:US-CA_type:waterbody_source:gnis|display=inline,title}} | type = [[Reservoir (water)|Reservoir]] | inflow = [[Trinity River (California)|Trinity River]] | outflow = [[Trinity River (California)|Trinity River]] | basin_countries = United States | length = | width = | area = {{convert|750|acre|abbr=on}} | depth = | max-depth = | volume = {{convert|14660|acre.ft|GL|abbr=on}} | residence_time = | elevation = {{convert|1903|ft|abbr=on}} | cities = [[Weaverville, California]] | references = }}
'''Lewiston Lake''' is a [[reservoir]] impounded by [[Lewiston Dam (California)|Lewiston Dam]] on the [[Trinity River (California)|Trinity River]], in [[Trinity County, California]].
==Geography== Lewiston Lake is near the towns of [[Weaverville, California|Weaverville]] and [[Lewiston, California|Lewiston]] in [[Trinity County, California]].
It is used for [[transbasin diversion]] to the [[Sacramento River]] and [[flood control]], as well as for [[hydroelectric]] generation. It is in the canyon between the [[Trinity Mountains]] and [[Marble Mountains (Siskiyou County)|Marble Mountains]] of the southern [[Klamath Mountains]] System.
==Recreation== Lewiston reservoir is within the Trinity Unit of the [[Whiskeytown-Shasta-Trinity National Recreation Area]], in the [[Shasta-Trinity National Forest]]. It is a popular destination for fishing, kayaking, and camping.
The [[California Office of Environmental Health Hazard Assessment]] (OEHHA) has developed a safe eating [https://oehha.ca.gov/advisories/lewiston-lake advisory] for Lewiston Lake based on levels of mercury or [[Polychlorinated biphenyl|PCBs]] found in fish caught from this water body.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://oehha.ca.gov/advisories/lewiston-lake|title=Lewiston Lake|last=Admin|first=OEHHA|date=2014-12-30|work=OEHHA|access-date=2018-06-13|language=en}}</ref>
