<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.sohu.com/20140527/n400116542.shtml | title=Cloud Nanlu hydropower gate was suddenly pulled away a total investment of 21.9 billion | publisher=Sohu | accessdate=2 June 2014 | language=Chinese}}</ref> In May 2014 reports surfaced that the dam and been damaged or was structurally unsound, forcing engineers to draw down the reservoir level and leaving the power station inoperable.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.scmp.com/article/1519858/vast-hydropower-station-left-idle-year-after-sluice-gate-ripped | title=Crippled HK$27 billion Jinsha River hydro plant badly built, says official | publisher=South China Morning Post | date=27 May 2014 | accessdate=2 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.gokunming.com/en/blog/item/3240/yunnan_dam_structurally_unsound_repairs_in_limbo | title=Yunnan dam structurally unsound, repairs in limbo | publisher=Go Kunming | date=28 May 2014 | accessdate=2 June 2014}}</ref> An estimated 16,900 people will be relocated after its construction.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.internationalrivers.org/china/jinsha-river/jinsha-river-dams|title=Jinsha River Dams|publisher=International Rivers|accessdate=9 January 2011}}</ref>
