{{italic title}}
[[File:TheNewNoah.jpg|thumb|First edition]]
'''''The New Noah''''' is a book written by British [[Natural history|naturalist]] and writer [[Gerald Durrell]].  It was first published by [[William Collins, Sons|Collins]] in 1955.<ref>{{Cite book |last=Durrell |first=Gerald |authorlink=Gerald Durrell |title=The New Noah |location=London |publisher=[[William Collins, Sons|Collins]] |year=1955 |OCLC=25436467 }}</ref>

The book is an account for older children of his various [[Exploration|expedition]]s to collect animals for zoos, to some extent an anthology of the best bits from various previous accounts.

